issue.title: Search doesn't pass titleBarActiveBackground to private API
issue.body:
Search accepts a `titleBarActiveBackground` param, but the code that hits the undocumented private API doesn't pass this value through. Assuming this is a one line fix, but since I don't have access to the API, I can't verify it myself to make the PR.

https://github.com/vscodethemes/web/blob/main/app/clients/api.ts#L33-L42

comment.body:
> take a screenshot as an input and magically identify the theme

That's the ultimate goal for this project (if I had the time). 

Some ideas of varying complexity I had on how to do this:
1. Select colors from a screenshot manually (might need to be a browser extension)
2. Upload a picture, extract the most dominant colors and search for themes with matching colors
3. Train an ML model to identify themes from VS Code screenshots

What do you think? Any other ways we could identify themes from a screenshot?

comment.body:
Thanks for the report! I just pushed a fix. 

Are you building something on top of this project or do you have very specific taste in themes? I'm surprised you noticed!

issue.title: Arrow Key Navigation
issue.body:
Thanks for such a nice site. Here is some feedback.

I like to use my keyboard as much as I can. I'm disappointed every time I visit a site that has pagination and does not support paging with the arrow keys.

Thanks,

comment.body:
Unfortunately I didn’t have much time to set this project up for external contributions when I last worked on it. I definitely want to though and will try to find time to make it easy for others to contribute soon. Thanks for offering. 

For keyboard pagination, do you have any examples of websites that you think do this well? 

I’m a bit concerned about people unexpectedly navigating away. What do you think about having to scroll to the end of the page first (so pagination is in view) before the left/right keys can be used to go to the prev/next page?

issue.title: [Question/Feature] Is there a way to use this code to generate images?
issue.body: I am developing a new theme for VSCode (and others eventually), and I include screenshots of the theme in action in the `README.md` for the project. Currently, I have to manually screenshot the theme by debugging it and screenshotting the development preview for each theme variant. I would love to be able to generate these automatically before the theme is published. Is there a way to do this for local themes, using your code?

comment.body:
Sorry for the late response. This isn't possible at the moment but a CLI could be built to generate the same preview images used on the site locally. 

If there's enough interest I'd consider building one or if anyone else is interested in contributing I'd be happy to help guide you.

issue.title: Arrow Key Navigation
issue.body:
Thanks for such a nice site. Here is some feedback.

I like to use my keyboard as much as I can. I'm disappointed every time I visit a site that has pagination and does not support paging with the arrow keys.

Thanks,

comment.body:
Unfortunately I didn’t have much time to set this project up for external contributions when I last worked on it. I definitely want to though and will try to find time to make it easy for others to contribute soon. Thanks for offering. 

For keyboard pagination, do you have any examples of websites that you think do this well? 

I’m a bit concerned about people unexpectedly navigating away. What do you think about having to scroll to the end of the page first (so pagination is in view) before the left/right keys can be used to go to the prev/next page?

issue.title: [Question/Feature] Is there a way to use this code to generate images?
issue.body: I am developing a new theme for VSCode (and others eventually), and I include screenshots of the theme in action in the `README.md` for the project. Currently, I have to manually screenshot the theme by debugging it and screenshotting the development preview for each theme variant. I would love to be able to generate these automatically before the theme is published. Is there a way to do this for local themes, using your code?

comment.body:
Sorry for the late response. This isn't possible at the moment but a CLI could be built to generate the same preview images used on the site locally. 

If there's enough interest I'd consider building one or if anyone else is interested in contributing I'd be happy to help guide you.

issue.title: Broken SVG
issue.body: https://vscodethemes.com/?text=XadillaX Clicking the image redirects to the correct image: https://vscodethemes.com/e/xadillax.van-gogh-paintings/starry-night?language=javascript Seems like the DB is returning theme slugs that don't exist in KV, causing the theme page to redirect to the first theme in the extension.
